{"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"@objc","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"setup","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"remoteConfiguration","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@M@SnowplowTracker@objc(cs)SPRemoteConfiguration","text":"RemoteConfiguration","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/SnowplowTracker\/documentation\/SnowplowTracker\/RemoteConfiguration"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"defaultConfiguration","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"defaultBundles","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": [","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@M@SnowplowTracker@objc(cs)SPConfigurationBundle","text":"ConfigurationBundle","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/SnowplowTracker\/documentation\/SnowplowTracker\/ConfigurationBundle"},{"text":"]?, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"defaultConfigurationVersion","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"defaultBundleVersion","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"text":" = NSInteger.min, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"onSuccess","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"@escaping","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ([","kind":"text"},{"text":"String","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS"},{"text":"]?, ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@M@SnowplowTracker@E@SPConfigurationState","text":"ConfigurationState","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/SnowplowTracker\/documentation\/SnowplowTracker\/ConfigurationState"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Void","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:s4Voida"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"parameters":[{"name":"remoteConfiguration","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The remote configuration used to indicate where to download the configuration from.","type":"text"}]}]},{"name":"defaultBundles","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The default configuration passed by default in case there isn’t a cached version and it’s able to download a new one."}]}]},{"name":"defaultBundleVersion","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Version of the default configuration that will be used to compare with the fetched remote config to decide whether to replace it."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"name":"onSuccess","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The callback called when a configuration (cached or downloaded) is set."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It passes two arguments: list of the namespaces associated to the created trackers"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and the state of the configuration – whether it was retrieved from cache or fetched over the network."}]}]}],"kind":"parameters"},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The app can run multiple tracker instances which will be identified by string ","type":"text"},{"code":"namespaces","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The trackers configuration is automatically download from the endpoint indicated in the ","type":"text"},{"code":"RemoteConfiguration","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"passed as argument. For more details see ","type":"text"},{"code":"RemoteConfiguration","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The method is asynchronous and you can receive the list of the created trackers in the callbacks once the trackers are created."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The callback can be called multiple times in case a cached configuration is ready and later a fetched configuration is available."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"You can also pass as argument a default configuration in case there isn’t a cached configuration and it’s not able to download"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a new one. The downloaded configuration updates the cached one only if the configuration version is greater than the cached one."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Otherwise the cached one is kept and the callback is not called."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"IMPORTANT: The EventStore will persist all the events that have been tracked but not yet sent.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Those events are attached to the namespace.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"If the tracker is removed or the app relaunched with a different namespace, those events can’t","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"be sent to the collector and they remain in a zombie state inside the EventStore.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"To remove all the zombie events you can call an internal method ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"removeUnsentEventsExceptForNamespaces"},{"text":" on ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SPSQLEventStore"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"which will delete all the EventStores instanced with namespaces not listed in the passed list.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/snowplowtracker\/snowplow\/setup(remoteconfiguration:defaultconfiguration:defaultconfigurationversion:onsuccess:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SnowplowTracker\/documentation\/SnowplowTracker\/Snowplow\/setup(remoteConfiguration:defaultConfiguration:defaultConfigurationVersion:onSuccess:)","interfaceLanguage":